It's 'cause my phone has no reception.

57
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:05,018
It wasn't the plan
for you to come all the way here.

58
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:10,106
Come look at this.

59
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:12,734
Ah. Yeah, that's him.

60
00:03:12,817 --> 00:03:15,111
Th… that's my dad's driver right there.

61
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:21,534
Do you recognize this address?

62
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:28,124
Oh! Out of the five addresses,
I know this one.

63
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:32,212
It… it's the last place my dad's driver
w… w… went to drop something off.

64
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,088
You have to tell the captain
everything you know.

65
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:35,298
Okay. I'll do it.

66
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,971
Yeah, I hear you. Go ahead.

67
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:43,556
I can talk right now.

68
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,766
Yun-sang's driving.

69
00:03:45,266 --> 00:03:47,644
Yeah. Can you hear me?

70
00:03:47,727 --> 00:03:48,895
-Yeah--
-Hello?

71
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,942
This is driving me crazy.

72
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:57,028
Hey, Captain, are you all right?

73
00:03:59,572 --> 00:04:03,243
18-1, GUGAK-RI, EUNGDEOK-MYEON
WOONGCHEON, GYEONGGI-DO

74
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,538
Did you get it?

75
00:04:07,622 --> 00:04:09,457
Oh! Whoa! Whoa!

76
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:11,417
Oh, a deer.

77
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:12,585
Thank God.

78
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:14,087
Oh!

79
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:16,714
You got my text, right?
We're on our way there.

80
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:17,882
Hello?

81
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:19,133
You there?

82
00:04:19,217 --> 00:04:21,177
In-a?

83
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:25,098
Officially, you're on
civilian protection duty.

84
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:26,849
The shortest route is an hour.

85
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,060
-Report to me in ten.
-Copy that.

86
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:30,520
Hyeon-jae.

87
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:31,938
Yes.

88
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:34,649
I'm worried. Are you sure you'll be okay?

89
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:36,150
I'm okay. Don't worry about us.

90
00:04:37,568 --> 00:04:39,237
-I'll be heading out, then.
-Okay.

91
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:07,056
-Where are you going?
-Eungdeok-myeon, Gugak-ri.

92
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:10,018
You have to go back.
Please turn around.

93
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,732
Who are you looking for?

94
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:20,069
Answer the question.

95
00:05:23,114 --> 00:05:25,074
Baek. We're here to see Father Baek.

96
00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:29,162
Father Baek has visitors.

97
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:31,706
Okay.

98
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:34,334
Let 'em through!

99
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:37,920
Hello, Father.

100
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:42,425
You seem to have some concerning guests.

101
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:20,797
Oh!

102
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:22,757
Se-kyung.

103
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:24,258
Yun-sang.

104
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:29,222
A little tough to find this place, huh?

105
00:06:30,431 --> 00:06:32,225
Goodness, you came all this way

106
00:06:33,017 --> 00:06:34,394
just to speak with me.

107
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,314
Right, Clara?

108
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:40,566
And Thomas.

109
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:44,529
So happy you're here. Mmm.

110
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:48,282
We sure have a lot to talk about,
don't we?

111
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:49,951
Ah.

112
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:51,744
Oh, wait.

113
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,455
Let's start off with confessional.

114
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,667
Don't the two of you have
your wedding coming up?

115
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:00,837
Ah, no, no, no, no.

116
00:07:02,338 --> 00:07:04,799
Confessional is one on one.

117
00:07:06,008 --> 00:07:09,220
You must stand alone right before God
and really confront yourself.

118
00:07:09,303 --> 00:07:10,388
That's not--

119
00:07:10,471 --> 00:07:12,515
You know, with confessions,

120
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:14,851
when it hasn't been done in a while,

121
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,479
it becomes quite difficult.

122
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:41,961
I know.

123
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:45,506
I know my actions will lead me to hell.

124
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:46,799
I'm a murderer,

125
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:49,427
and it's happened three times now.

126
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:51,304
Sh! Hey.

127
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:53,806
Clara.

128
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:56,392
Now, what did I always say?

129
00:07:57,393 --> 00:08:01,147
If you don't complete your homework
on time, it'll eventually catch up to you.

130
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:02,857
And the next thing you know,

131
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:04,525
you're overwhelmed with sin.

132
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:08,613
It's as if you have scabs
all over your body.

133
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:25,129
But even with sin,

134
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:28,007
God will always forgive you.

135
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:29,550
Every time.

136
00:08:30,801 --> 00:08:33,721
God's forgiveness is endless and kind.

137
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:35,848
He never tires.

138
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:38,184
Instead, he always waits patiently.

139
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:44,106
Yeah, I understand that,

140
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:46,234
but I have no desire to repent.

141
00:08:50,446 --> 00:08:51,531
Well, all right.

142
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:54,617
I will pray for you

143
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,370
to absolve you of sin.

144
00:08:57,995 --> 00:09:02,291
Clara, you still must reflect, repent,

145
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,919
and find the resolve to not sin again.

146
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:07,547
God will wait for you

147
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:10,007
with love and patience.

148
00:09:17,473 --> 00:09:19,600
Well then, what about you?

149
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,315
God is speaking to me.

150
00:09:27,775 --> 00:09:29,694
You two have a purpose.

151
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:34,365
You may not think it so,
but God always knows.

152
00:09:34,991 --> 00:09:38,911
It can indeed be difficult
to discern God's true intentions.

153
00:09:39,745 --> 00:09:41,998
But the fact that we're here together

154
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:44,250
must mean something, wouldn't you agree?

155
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,378
On the way in,

156
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:49,380
I'd hoped that you weren't in here

157
00:09:50,006 --> 00:09:51,966
'cause I had to believe it wasn't true.

158
00:09:52,049 --> 00:09:52,967
That you'd--

159
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:56,721
I'm not sure what you have planned, but…

160
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:00,725
stop hiding out here, Father.

161
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:05,062
You have to explain to everyone
why you abandoned the church so suddenly.

162
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:18,034
Yun-sang.

163
00:10:20,661 --> 00:10:22,580
Widen your horizons, child.

164
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,543
The outcome you seek…

165
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:32,840
…is reductive in nature and lacks wisdom.

166
00:10:36,093 --> 00:10:37,845
Please.

167
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:42,433
It's not just us. So many people
have been hurt by your actions.

168
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:47,730
The end is near now.
They deserve closure, don't you think?

169
00:10:50,358 --> 00:10:53,444
I know a four-year-old
who's envious of his older sister

170
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:56,322
'cause she's seven,
and he'll never get to be.

171
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:58,074
Have some empathy.

172
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:00,910
Don't your believers
deserve some compassion?

173
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:03,329
All of us.
We all trusted you to protect us.

174
00:11:10,419 --> 00:11:13,297
Let's stick to the original plan.
Mm-hmm.

175
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:19,679
I'll prepare a plan B as well.

176
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:24,225
Yep, yep.

177
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:39,615
The best servants of God,

178
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:43,119
they are the ones who will go.

179
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:46,664
There is not much time to waste.

180
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,793
I trust you, Yun-sang.

181
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:54,088
I know you will make the wise choice.

182
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:57,800
On the day we leave…

183
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:02,972
an hour in advance, be ready.

184
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:04,515
I will rescue you.

185
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:21,532
Oh.

186
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:25,244
You went outside?
Can't remember the last time you were out.

187
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:28,914
You know, I was visiting my good friend.

188
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:30,916
Ah good. Yeah.

189
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,794
You ought to.
Getting some fresh air is nice.

190
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:36,505
-Isn't it better than your bedroom?
-Mmm.

191
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:48,434
G… G… Grandma? I was…

192
00:12:49,393 --> 00:12:50,269
Huh?

193
00:12:50,352 --> 00:12:52,605
I, uh…

194
00:12:52,688 --> 00:12:53,939
Please don't leave me.

195
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:55,232
Huh?

196
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:59,361
Oh, now, what would make you say that?

197
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,655
Uh, my dad's, uh…

198
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:04,325
Well… well, his driver told me, uh,

199
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:09,121
you and I have to
move to Dad's official residence.

200
00:13:09,205 --> 00:13:10,790
Don't mind him, In-tae.

201
00:13:13,042 --> 00:13:16,295
The nerve. Spewing nonsense like that.

202
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,925
I would never abandon my grandson.

203
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:22,510
Though I would leave your dad.

204
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:26,889
-Don't worry too much now.
-Okay.

205
00:13:26,972 --> 00:13:28,724
-Go get some rest.
-Mmm.

206
00:13:41,278 --> 00:13:43,614
I had wished to provide you an escort,

207
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:46,200
but it seems that won't be necessary.

208
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:47,952
Oh.

209
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:54,375
A soldier will be driving you guys back.
Captain's orders.

210
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,170
Everyone on board!

211
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:00,047
Good luck, both of you.

212
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:01,799
And please,

213
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,885
I pray your choice will be wise.

214
00:14:20,901 --> 00:14:22,152
Come on, Father!

215
00:14:25,739 --> 00:14:26,699
Just open the door!

216
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:33,038
-Father!
-Give me something.

217
00:14:40,754 --> 00:14:43,048
Just one word. Please, I'm begging you.

218
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:50,681
Just enough for me to carry on.

219
