220
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:19,710
-Hey.
-Found a CD.

221
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:21,545
I found this.

222
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:23,839
Ooh! We can put videos in that.

223
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,341
-Mmm.
-Good find.

224
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:29,970
I heard that Netflix
won't be coming out with any new content,

225
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,138
not even in the US.

226
00:15:31,221 --> 00:15:33,390
Yeah. Why would they these days?

227
00:15:33,474 --> 00:15:35,976
There's no point
in making movies right now.

228
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,145
Yeah, I don't think
we'll get another season.

229
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:41,982
There's still a lot of weird directors
that wanna film their stuff,

230
00:15:42,066 --> 00:15:44,026
but they don't have
any actors willing to work.

231
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:46,820
That makes sense to me.
Why act when the world is ending?

232
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:48,530
Yeah, I wouldn't act either.

233
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:50,324
Why else would they keep working?

234
00:15:50,407 --> 00:15:52,034
For more money, obviously.

235
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:55,579
Wait, what?

236
00:15:58,207 --> 00:15:59,917
Why are there so many people here?

237
00:16:00,584 --> 00:16:01,961
I don't know.

238
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:05,172
-These guys have different uniforms too.
-Let's go to Ms. Jin.

239
00:16:05,255 --> 00:16:06,548
-Yeah. Let's go. This way.
-Okay.

240
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:08,300
-You there!
-Hurry.

241
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:10,552
-Off the platform!
-Hurry up!

242
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:28,362
So the center's planning with the US.

243
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:35,577
-Are you--
-Are you gonna be--

244
00:16:38,038 --> 00:16:38,872
Go ahead.

245
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:40,165
The training center.

246
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,210
With what went on,
I heard a rumor around the base

247
00:16:43,293 --> 00:16:44,628
that you'd be dismissed.

248
00:16:49,758 --> 00:16:51,176
Don't worry about me.

249
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:53,429
So Young-ji…

250
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:56,598
-Have you seen her since that day?
-Huh?

251
00:16:57,099 --> 00:16:58,642
Nope. I haven't seen her a single time.

252
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:02,855
-It didn't seem like she had a cell phone.
-I guess so. It's okay, ma'am.

253
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:13,073
This airfield is packed
with division-level security right now.

254
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:14,408
If my instincts are correct,

255
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:16,618
they're definitely
planning something here.

256
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:19,663
I think they're trying to get
the remaining citizens home.

257
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:21,373
There's still a lot of Americans in Korea.

258
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,250
You're kidding me.

259
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,918
Hold on a minute.

260
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:26,628
The airstrip, right?

261
00:17:28,088 --> 00:17:29,631
The US military base.

262
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:31,425
It has to be that!

263
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:33,594
Right. That makes sense.

264
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:36,096
I guess Sister Regina was right about it.

265
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:38,557
They're really moving up everything.

266
00:17:39,308 --> 00:17:40,934
Uh, excuse me.

267
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:43,937
Se-kyung, can I speak to you?

268
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,439
Uh, oh.

269
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:46,857
Okay.

270
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:53,280
So, Father,
what are you planning to do now?

271
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,741
We have to do something,

272
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:58,452
and it's gotta be more
than prayers this time around.

273
00:17:58,535 --> 00:17:59,995
Yun-sang.

274
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:02,372
Did Father Baek say anything else
to you during your visit?

275
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:04,666
He knows about the fire
at the church, right?

276
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:12,132
Here.

277
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:14,343
It's been a while.

278
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:19,348
When are you and Yun-sang leaving?

279
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:24,895
Se-kyung.

280
00:18:25,687 --> 00:18:26,814
Mmm. What's up?

281
00:18:28,273 --> 00:18:29,650
I wanted to ask.

282
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,278
Did In-a ever say anything to you

283
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:36,156
about In-seong?

284
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,324
You can tell me.

285
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:39,159
In-seong oppa?

286
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:43,247
Did she ever tell you

287
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:46,083
how In-seong died?

288
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:48,335
It was an accident, right? At the riot?

289
00:18:48,418 --> 00:18:49,419
Mm-mm.

290
00:18:52,005 --> 00:18:53,590
I guess I'll tell you, then.

291
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:58,554
After the riot,
most of the food was all gone.

292
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:02,516
In-a just disappeared.
She had to leave with her unit.

293
00:19:05,352 --> 00:19:08,230
We couldn't reach her,
and In-seong was impatient.

294
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:11,733
He left to look for food one day.

295
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:14,820
He drove around everywhere.

296
00:19:16,655 --> 00:19:18,949
He was downtown.

297
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:28,876
Those beasts, they murdered him.

298
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:30,961
He never had a chance.

299
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:33,338
My poor boy.

300
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,215
Killed just like that.

301
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:41,972
Murdered in daylight.

302
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:46,143
They got him in the red-light district
right near that brothel.

303
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:54,234
A parishioner
who'd done business there told me

304
00:19:55,402 --> 00:19:58,530
she saw a tall, thin person there
behind In-seong.

305
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:01,783
And then, he…

306
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:10,834
So I told In-a.

307
00:20:11,627 --> 00:20:12,669
And she

308
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:14,755
just said that

309
00:20:15,797 --> 00:20:17,007
it could've been anyone.

310
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:20,135
A lot of people are tall and thin,
and that I shouldn't think about it.

311
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,304
That I should just carry on with my life

312
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:24,973
'cause there wasn't much that I could do.

313
00:20:26,975 --> 00:20:28,352
So, sure, I thought.

314
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:30,979
There's not much time left anyway.

315
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:32,397
The clock's ticking.

316
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:35,859
So I told myself not to think about it,

317
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:38,820
but then these guys
just kept dying one after the other.

318
00:20:38,904 --> 00:20:41,823
I felt like someone was trying
to get revenge for In-seong.

319
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:43,158
Justice, if you will.

320
00:20:44,701 --> 00:20:45,577
I thought that…

321
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:04,930
In-a could never just let anything go.

322
00:21:05,013 --> 00:21:06,223
Always so stubborn.

323
00:21:13,563 --> 00:21:14,898
Your daughter's a hero.

324
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:17,526
In-a

325
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:20,112
would do anything to keep us safe.

326
00:21:20,195 --> 00:21:21,071
Anything.

327
00:21:25,701 --> 00:21:26,827
Yeah.

328
00:21:28,662 --> 00:21:29,955
Do you think it's In-a?

329
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:30,998
Yeah.

330
00:21:36,545 --> 00:21:38,714
What a world we live in, huh?

331
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,132
Filled with revenge.

332
00:21:42,551 --> 00:21:45,137
And everyone knows that revenge

333
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:49,057
can never be forgiven by God.

334
00:22:03,071 --> 00:22:05,073
Mess Sergeant, good work.

335
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:14,291
Does she have to stay around for this?

336
00:22:15,208 --> 00:22:16,835
No, it'd be better without her.

337
00:22:18,378 --> 00:22:19,755
Please head back first, then.

338
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:26,970
I heard Mess Sergeant So Ju-yeon

339
00:22:27,054 --> 00:22:29,097
used to be a part of
the Special Missions Unit

340
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:30,474
before transferring.

341
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:32,768
She a buddy of yours?

342
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,436
Hmm?

343
00:22:42,652 --> 00:22:44,654
You've been coming here too much.

344
00:22:45,447 --> 00:22:49,409
How can I not when there've been
so many unreported operations?

345
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:51,870
-There's been just one.
-What about the missing ammunition?

346
00:22:51,953 --> 00:22:53,705
Uh, that's already been addressed--

347
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:57,209
You know very well
that the ammunition was meant for the SMU.

348
00:22:57,709 --> 00:22:59,544
So don't even bother lying.

349
00:23:00,670 --> 00:23:01,838
Yeah?

350
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:07,135
-Search the place!
-Yes, sir.

351
00:23:09,346 --> 00:23:10,722
299 DAYS UNTIL ASTEROID COLLISION

352
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:12,808
Look at all the cars back there!

353
00:23:13,308 --> 00:23:15,811
Let us pass!
We've been stuck here for hours!

354
00:23:15,894 --> 00:23:17,521
The soldiers are blocking it!

355
00:23:17,604 --> 00:23:18,605
Move it!

356
00:23:19,314 --> 00:23:20,357
Still standing by.

357
00:23:20,857 --> 00:23:23,151
It looks like they're stopping traffic
with a blockade.

358
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:24,611
A coup from the military.

359
00:23:25,278 --> 00:23:28,365
It's a strategic takeover of our weapons.
We've got a mutiny now.

360
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:30,117
Those guys will try anything.

361
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:33,036
A few commanders have joined in as well,
so take caution.

362
00:23:41,294 --> 00:23:43,004
Our unit won't be engaging.

363
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:45,507
The battalion's orders
are to guard the VIPs.

364
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:46,925
Understood?

365
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:53,974
I'm Major Jang, the aide-de-camp
to the division commander. Let us pass.

366
00:23:54,057 --> 00:23:55,183
Yes, sir!

367
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:59,396
Let's go. Let 'em through.
It's all right. Come on.

368
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:04,109
Let us pass!
We've been stuck here for hours!

369
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:06,903
We're gonna break through
the opposite lane.

370
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:21,460
What the hell?

371
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:22,919
Sir.

372
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:26,214
That son of a bitch just ran off!

373
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:29,092
I should've known he'd do that.
Jesus Christ!

374
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,811
Ah!

375
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:41,688
-Oh, my leg!
-Ju-yeon!

376
00:24:41,771 --> 00:24:43,815
-My leg. Help!
-Ju-yeon, are you okay?

377
00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:46,568
Come on! We gotta stop the bleeding!
Hey, Hyeon-sik! Come here!

378
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:48,028
Help us.

379
00:24:48,778 --> 00:24:50,197
-Come on! Come on!
-Ah!

380
00:24:50,822 --> 00:24:53,200
General!

381
00:24:53,283 --> 00:24:55,410
You okay, sir?

382
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:57,162
General! General!

383
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:02,334
The rebel leaders are running away.
We need to stop them.

384
00:25:05,212 --> 00:25:07,380
Special Missions Unit,
all withdraw!

385
00:25:07,464 --> 00:25:08,423
Sir!

386
00:25:11,718 --> 00:25:14,012
I repeat. SMU, we need to retreat!

387
00:25:14,095 --> 00:25:16,681
I can't follow an order
that lets the rebels escape.

388
00:25:16,765 --> 00:25:18,808
-You're kidding?
-We're shooting warning shots.

389
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:20,227
Open fire.

390
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:22,270
Come on, get back!

391
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:26,233
Come on!

392
00:25:32,447 --> 00:25:34,366
Cease fire! Cease fire!

393
00:25:34,991 --> 00:25:38,119
The penalty for insubordination
during wartime is death!

394
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:39,329
Captain Kang!

395
00:25:39,913 --> 00:25:40,956
Kang In-a!

396
00:25:45,293 --> 00:25:47,837
Okay, ladies, still hungry?

397
00:25:48,338 --> 00:25:49,506
Plenty for you to eat.

398
00:25:50,465 --> 00:25:53,969
The world may be ending soon,
but food's still important.

399
00:25:54,052 --> 00:25:56,096
That's it. Yeah, that's right.

400
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:00,559
-Mess Sergeant.
-Hmm?

401
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:01,768
Is everything okay?

402
00:26:03,436 --> 00:26:04,437
They let you go?

403
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:12,195
You know, after you left,
the JIU went through our snacks.

404
00:26:12,279 --> 00:26:13,238
Not sure why.

405
00:26:15,782 --> 00:26:16,658
Hey, Pang.

406
00:26:17,325 --> 00:26:18,159
Yeah?

407
00:26:18,952 --> 00:26:19,869
All right.

408
00:26:23,540 --> 00:26:24,791
We got things to do.

409
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:27,752
Okay. Go double time.

410
00:26:27,836 --> 00:26:30,255
I need all these potatoes.
Take everything.

411
00:26:30,338 --> 00:26:32,507
Are we seriously taking everything?

412
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:33,925
-Yep!
-There's so many.

413
00:26:34,009 --> 00:26:37,637
You see? Does anyone happen to know
how to make all these multiply?

414
00:26:37,721 --> 00:26:38,888
You got me beat.

415
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:41,057
First, take your potato. Okay.

416
00:26:42,392 --> 00:26:45,103
You see where all the buds
are clumped together over here?

417
00:26:45,186 --> 00:26:48,982
You just cut out a little piece
that's around there.

418
00:26:49,065 --> 00:26:51,109
Keep about two or three. Just like that.

419
00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:54,988
And then, add some ash to it
from your firewood.

420
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:57,240
The ash is there
as the potato's protector.

421
00:26:57,324 --> 00:27:00,577
You put it here.
And by doing so, it'll shield it.

422
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:01,745
Got it?

423
00:27:01,828 --> 00:27:04,289
So now we can plant them
right into the ground.

424
00:27:05,624 --> 00:27:08,335
Wait until summertime,
and these spuds will taste delicious.

425
00:27:08,418 --> 00:27:10,170
Good plan.

426
00:27:10,253 --> 00:27:11,421
That'll be good.

427
00:27:11,921 --> 00:27:14,883
Except, as we all know,
we won't have a next summer.

428
00:27:14,966 --> 00:27:16,009
Oops!

429
00:27:17,927 --> 00:27:20,055
I guess so-- It's hard to--

430
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:23,892
You know.
I don't like thinking about it too much.

431
00:27:23,975 --> 00:27:25,310
Yeah, I try to forget.

432
00:27:28,146 --> 00:27:30,482
-Hey, guys. What are we making today?
-Some pancakes.

433
00:27:30,565 --> 00:27:31,733
With potatoes?

434
00:27:31,816 --> 00:27:33,485
-You wanna make pancakes?
-You're uptight.

435
00:27:41,951 --> 00:27:43,536
Why are we doing this out here?

436
00:27:48,541 --> 00:27:49,542
This good enough for you?

437
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:52,504
Yeah, I guess. Pass it over.

438
00:28:06,184 --> 00:28:08,144
Can you even shoot, huh?

439
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:10,313
I can, so come on.

440
00:28:10,897 --> 00:28:12,148
Just give the gun to me.

441
00:28:20,365 --> 00:28:21,324
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

442
00:28:22,283 --> 00:28:23,451
You gotta be careful.

443
00:28:30,333 --> 00:28:32,127
This gun better not be fake.

444
00:28:59,446 --> 00:29:00,405
Yeah!

445
00:29:05,034 --> 00:29:07,620
Meow, meow.

446
00:29:07,704 --> 00:29:08,663
Meow.

447
00:29:09,789 --> 00:29:11,166
-Huh?
-Hey!

448
00:29:15,170 --> 00:29:16,254
-What's this about?
-Come on!

449
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:20,049
Now get out!

450
00:29:20,133 --> 00:29:21,676
No! No, no!

451
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:24,179
-No, no, no, no!
-Is she out of her mind? The fuck is this?

452
00:29:24,262 --> 00:29:25,597
-Damn it!
-You won't get by!

453
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:26,681
Huh?

454
00:29:28,099 --> 00:29:29,142
Oh, okay.

455
00:29:29,726 --> 00:29:32,103
I just need the time and place to meet.

456
00:29:32,187 --> 00:29:33,229
Okay.

457
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:38,234
Listen to me.

458
00:29:39,569 --> 00:29:40,904
And trust Daddy's plan.

459
00:29:41,488 --> 00:29:43,448
We're out of time, okay?

460
00:29:44,365 --> 00:29:46,367
They're getting a chartered plane.

461
00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:47,744
We need to get on it.

462
00:29:49,329 --> 00:29:53,041
And once we do,
there won't be anything to worry about.

463
00:29:55,752 --> 00:29:59,088
'Cause everything is just fine.

464
00:30:01,841 --> 00:30:03,968
Anything wrong, honey?

465
00:30:06,262 --> 00:30:08,181
Ha-yul?

466
00:31:09,784 --> 00:31:11,286
That motherfucker.

467
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:16,374
They're all the same.

468
00:31:50,575 --> 00:31:52,952
I know my actions
will lead me to hell.

469
00:31:53,036 --> 00:31:54,495
I'm a murderer,

470
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:56,581
and it's happened three times now.

471
00:32:21,439 --> 00:32:23,399
The best servants of God,

472
00:32:24,817 --> 00:32:26,736
they are the ones who will go.

473
00:32:27,362 --> 00:32:29,322
There's not much time to waste.

474
00:32:32,033 --> 00:32:33,451
On the day we leave…

475
00:32:35,453 --> 00:32:38,581
an hour in advance, be ready.

476
00:32:39,165 --> 00:32:40,208
I will rescue you.

477
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:46,589
I trust you, Yun-sang.

478
00:32:46,673 --> 00:32:49,050
I know you will make the wise choice.

479
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:06,818
There they go again.

480
00:33:19,122 --> 00:33:20,248
Se-kyung.

481
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:24,085
Do you know what's happening?

482
00:33:26,671 --> 00:33:30,258
Why they're here,
circling the area over and over again?

483
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:36,139
You've probably already heard.

484
00:33:37,765 --> 00:33:38,850
It's true, then?

485
00:33:38,933 --> 00:33:41,894
They're really planning to leave?
There's another aircraft?

486
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:43,980
I don't know.

487
00:33:44,564 --> 00:33:45,523
Either way…

488
00:33:47,942 --> 00:33:49,861
it can only leave if it takes off.

489
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:52,071
Why wouldn't it?

490
00:33:52,947 --> 00:33:53,781
Huh?

491
00:34:07,628 --> 00:34:08,463
Se-kyung.

492
00:34:08,546 --> 00:34:11,424
-Yun-sang. I'll be right back.
-Hmm?

493
00:34:23,936 --> 00:34:24,979
I see.

494
00:34:26,397 --> 00:34:28,649
Why didn't you say anything, hmm?

495
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:32,737
I was embarrassed.

496
00:34:34,947 --> 00:34:37,867
Even though everyone already knows
how shameless my dad is.

497
00:34:38,493 --> 00:34:39,410
Ha-yul.

498
00:34:46,501 --> 00:34:47,752
Always remember

499
00:34:48,628 --> 00:34:50,379
that your number one priority

500
00:34:51,339 --> 00:34:52,423
is yourself.

501
00:34:54,550 --> 00:34:56,427
-But you're not like that.
-Mm-mm.

502
00:34:57,261 --> 00:34:58,763
That's true for everyone.

503
00:35:00,348 --> 00:35:01,390
Me included.

504
00:35:02,683 --> 00:35:04,727
I have to take care of myself

505
00:35:05,853 --> 00:35:07,396
so that I can care for you,

506
00:35:08,147 --> 00:35:09,732
So-min, and Jin-seo.

507
00:35:14,028 --> 00:35:15,488
You're precious, okay?

508
00:35:16,572 --> 00:35:18,116
Your classmates were too.

509
00:35:20,243 --> 00:35:21,244
Got it?

510
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:29,293
You can cry.

511
00:35:29,377 --> 00:35:30,962
Come here. It's all right.

512
00:35:33,714 --> 00:35:35,091
You're okay, Ha-yul.

513
00:36:15,047 --> 00:36:17,341
You shouldn't be here, In-a.

514
00:36:18,885 --> 00:36:22,096
Don't say that when you've already
prepared all of these supplies for us.

515
00:36:23,472 --> 00:36:27,435
Besides, even though this is important,
I have another thing to discuss with you.

516
00:36:30,188 --> 00:36:32,023
I have a plan, but I need your help.

517
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:36,360
I heard about everything.

518
00:36:38,237 --> 00:36:40,865
It was a good move for your unit
to raid the training center.

519
00:36:40,948 --> 00:36:42,742
And even though
it was probably an accident,

520
00:36:42,825 --> 00:36:44,911
it's a good thing
your friend was there too.

521
00:36:45,661 --> 00:36:47,580
They took all of that as a signal.

522
00:36:49,749 --> 00:36:53,085
They're cracking down now.
The JIU is questioning everyone.

523
00:36:53,169 --> 00:36:54,295
That's right.

524
00:36:54,879 --> 00:36:57,924
The JIU is getting antsy, not knowing
where all of that ammunition is.

525
00:36:58,007 --> 00:36:59,967
Yeah, I bet.

526
00:37:00,051 --> 00:37:03,012
They're searching
every nook and cranny of the base.

527
00:37:03,095 --> 00:37:05,514
And then you come in
with this conveniently timed raid?

528
00:37:05,598 --> 00:37:06,432
Correct.

529
00:37:06,515 --> 00:37:09,977
They're trying everything they can
to connect the ammunition to the SMU.

530
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:13,314
So all your ammunition
has been taken away, then?

531
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:17,276
Yeah. I'm not sure of the plan's details.
I just know it's gonna be big.

532
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:20,029
They've been organizing this for a while.

533
00:37:20,112 --> 00:37:22,365
That can only mean one thing,
don't you think?

534
00:37:25,409 --> 00:37:26,244
They're leaving.

535
00:38:02,071 --> 00:38:04,198
There's been a change of plans.

536
00:38:05,324 --> 00:38:08,869
Before we can evacuate,
we must rescue all of our children.

537
00:38:09,996 --> 00:38:12,290
You all need to be ready
at a moment's notice.

538
00:38:12,915 --> 00:38:14,542
Wait for my call to leave.

539
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:17,003
Until then,

540
00:38:18,045 --> 00:38:20,548
leaving this building is now prohibited.

541
00:38:23,718 --> 00:38:26,887
Over here. And so what about our kids?
Are they joining us?

542
00:38:26,971 --> 00:38:29,098
I need my kids. I can't leave alone.

543
00:38:29,765 --> 00:38:30,766
I hear you.

544
00:38:31,600 --> 00:38:33,477
I understand your concerns.

545
00:38:33,978 --> 00:38:35,396
There's no need to worry.

546
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,898
I will retrieve your children.

547
00:38:39,442 --> 00:38:43,237
As long as you're ready,
you'll all be on the plane.

548
00:38:44,905 --> 00:38:46,824
We'll break away from disease and war.

549
00:38:49,577 --> 00:38:52,538
And together,
all shall arrive at a new heaven,

550
00:38:52,621 --> 00:38:53,622
a new beginning!

551
00:38:54,832 --> 00:38:55,958
All of us…

552
00:38:57,960 --> 00:38:59,337
as God's chosen.

553
00:39:05,259 --> 00:39:07,511
-How's that feel?
-Still examining him?

554
00:39:07,595 --> 00:39:09,805
That's okay? And here?

555
00:39:09,889 --> 00:39:10,973
Ah!

556
00:39:11,057 --> 00:39:12,767
-Right there?
-Yeah.

557
00:39:12,850 --> 00:39:15,144
-When I press down or pull away?
-Ah!

558
00:39:15,227 --> 00:39:17,605
-They both hurt.
-Both, huh?

559
00:39:21,734 --> 00:39:23,944
There's a lot of inflammation.

560
00:39:24,028 --> 00:39:25,863
-Seems like appendicitis.
-Appendicitis--

561
00:39:25,946 --> 00:39:28,157
You've been in pain for a while,
haven't you?

562
00:39:30,034 --> 00:39:31,660
I tried to say it hurt.

563
00:39:31,744 --> 00:39:33,621
-Yeah. Uh…
-Oh.

564
00:39:33,704 --> 00:39:35,581
They would always say,
"We can't help you."

565
00:39:35,664 --> 00:39:37,541
"Wait till we arrive,
and he'll get surgery."

566
00:39:38,959 --> 00:39:40,711
When's he getting discharged?

567
00:39:41,212 --> 00:39:43,339
We need to wait
for his ultrasound results.

568
00:39:43,422 --> 00:39:46,008
We can't just let him go.
You'll have to wait.

569
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:51,263
All right? I'll proceed with
the abdominal ultrasound.

570
00:39:51,347 --> 00:39:52,348
Okay.

571
00:39:56,727 --> 00:39:58,312
How are you feeling?

572
00:40:00,981 --> 00:40:03,150
