IN THE TREATMENT ROOM

573
00:40:07,113 --> 00:40:08,948
Okay, here we go.

574
00:40:09,824 --> 00:40:12,118
Just like that. There.

575
00:40:18,999 --> 00:40:21,168
I'm losing my touch here.

576
00:40:22,670 --> 00:40:25,005
Ah shit. Okay.

577
00:40:25,089 --> 00:40:26,424
Ah! Uh…

578
00:40:26,507 --> 00:40:27,967
Oh. Uh…

579
00:40:32,513 --> 00:40:33,472
Ma'am.

580
00:40:35,015 --> 00:40:36,684
Go get the children.

581
00:40:37,685 --> 00:40:38,936
Uh, well…

582
00:40:39,562 --> 00:40:40,771
The boy is, uh…

583
00:40:40,855 --> 00:40:41,772
He's not healthy.

584
00:40:41,856 --> 00:40:43,566
I said to get them!

585
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:45,860
Do I make myself clear?

586
00:40:56,078 --> 00:40:58,247
At it again, already?

587
00:40:59,039 --> 00:41:00,166
Don't they eat?

588
00:41:01,709 --> 00:41:03,878
Hey! Hey, Seong-u?

589
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:05,546
Yes, Sergeant?

590
00:41:05,629 --> 00:41:07,631
Just make sure
you don't overcook the rice.

591
00:41:07,715 --> 00:41:09,175
-I won't.
-Thanks.

592
00:41:09,258 --> 00:41:10,718
-Hey, Pang.
-Yeah?

593
00:41:10,801 --> 00:41:13,137
You know what to do
with the aged sesame seeds?

594
00:41:13,220 --> 00:41:14,930
-What?
-Aged sesame seeds!

595
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:16,724
-Yeah.
-Mix it all at once.

596
00:41:20,144 --> 00:41:21,061
Here we go.

597
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:23,731
-Hey, listen up!
-Yes, what is it?

598
00:41:23,814 --> 00:41:26,901
We take over the night shift
starting at nineteen hours.

599
00:41:28,694 --> 00:41:31,614
-Ji-myeong! Code words?
-Sir? There's no dog hole.

600
00:41:31,697 --> 00:41:33,866
-So we all know those, right?
-Yes!

601
00:41:33,949 --> 00:41:35,951
We still don't have
bullets in our guns.

602
00:41:36,035 --> 00:41:37,286
Hit 'em in the head.

603
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:39,121
How do we do guard duty
without bullets?

604
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:42,124
I know that. Okay. Here we go.

605
00:41:43,209 --> 00:41:44,168
Get 'em up!

606
00:41:44,251 --> 00:41:45,669
There's no ammunition.

607
00:41:45,753 --> 00:41:47,755
Makes it hard for us to do guard duty.

608
00:41:49,465 --> 00:41:50,841
You're connected.

609
00:41:52,009 --> 00:41:54,094
Hello? This is Kang In-a speaking.

610
00:41:54,178 --> 00:41:56,597
Tell me what's going on.
Why are there so many helicopters?

611
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:59,099
Matters regarding the US
are under Martial Law Command.

612
00:41:59,183 --> 00:42:00,518
Are you disobeying orders?

613
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:03,354
I'm not challenging
the Martial Law Command.

614
00:42:03,437 --> 00:42:04,647
Who is it?

615
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:06,357
Captain Kang In-a.

616
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:08,484
I'm calling because
there's anxiety in the community.

617
00:42:08,567 --> 00:42:10,194
Civilians deserve to know what's going on.

618
00:42:10,277 --> 00:42:12,738
Lower-level units
have no access to this information.

619
00:42:15,449 --> 00:42:17,159
But as I said, the pe--

620
00:42:24,917 --> 00:42:26,752
They're not gonna tell us anything.

621
00:42:27,419 --> 00:42:29,088
Uh, what now?

622
00:42:29,171 --> 00:42:30,881
They still need their food, right?

623
00:42:32,716 --> 00:42:34,802
Take a look around
when you bring them their snacks.

624
00:42:36,762 --> 00:42:38,138
I like your plan.

625
00:42:50,109 --> 00:42:53,028
EMERGENCY AIRSTRIP

626
00:42:59,868 --> 00:43:01,120
I'm at the church.

627
00:43:26,687 --> 00:43:27,521
Ma'am.

628
00:43:28,147 --> 00:43:28,981
Hello, sir.

629
00:43:29,648 --> 00:43:30,733
State your business.

630
00:43:32,192 --> 00:43:34,778
We're here with
the Combat Support Company.

631
00:43:34,862 --> 00:43:37,072
I hear there are
no night shift changes tonight.

632
00:43:37,156 --> 00:43:38,699
Does your team need a snack?

633
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:42,494
We had a bunch left over
that our unit didn't need.

634
00:43:48,709 --> 00:43:51,045
Hey!
Late-night snacks over here!

635
00:43:51,128 --> 00:43:52,087
Come and get it!

636
00:43:52,671 --> 00:43:54,214
Enjoy.

637
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:55,549
-Wait, there's food?
-Hurry!

638
00:43:55,633 --> 00:43:57,301
Yeah!

639
00:44:16,278 --> 00:44:17,488
Okay.

640
00:44:17,571 --> 00:44:19,907
Hey, bring this cord
to that walkie over there.

641
00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:24,078
The time and place
might not be accurate,

642
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:26,872
but, uh, the house, the training center…

643
00:44:28,248 --> 00:44:30,834
If they're flying out,
the military base seems most likely.

644
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:34,254
But the boarding location
could still change.

645
00:44:35,047 --> 00:44:37,466
Father Baek said something
when we visited.

646
00:44:39,718 --> 00:44:41,261
He wants to get Yun-sang.

647
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:43,639
He said he'll stop by
an hour before they take off.

648
00:44:44,223 --> 00:44:46,058
-Yun-sang?
-Yeah.

649
00:44:46,141 --> 00:44:48,394
He said Yun-sang was important
for the escape.

650
00:44:51,438 --> 00:44:53,649
So it might not be
at the US base?

651
00:44:54,316 --> 00:44:55,693
Maybe it's a private plane, then.

652
00:44:55,776 --> 00:44:56,819
Wait a minute.

653
00:44:57,653 --> 00:45:00,447
If it's one hour away
from where Father Baek is,

654
00:45:01,824 --> 00:45:03,701
it could be the other one too.

655
00:45:03,784 --> 00:45:07,246
There's an emergency airstrip big enough
for both military and private planes.

656
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:09,498
So there's a chance the US one is a decoy.

657
00:45:09,581 --> 00:45:11,625
Yeah. Well, we've narrowed it down.

658
00:45:11,709 --> 00:45:14,378
And my guess is that
Father Baek is already on his way there.

659
00:45:14,461 --> 00:45:17,798
As for the training center,
there hasn't been any movement yet.

660
00:45:18,841 --> 00:45:22,052
Sister, I think you should check again
with your source.

661
00:45:22,136 --> 00:45:23,429
Yeah, that's a good idea.

662
00:45:24,304 --> 00:45:26,390
Okay, I'll call you back
when there's news.

663
00:45:26,473 --> 00:45:29,351
You received the device, right?
Keep it on you.

664
00:45:33,355 --> 00:45:36,442
Just in case something happens
to Captain Kang. Take this.

665
00:45:36,525 --> 00:45:38,694
Okay, I think we've got it.
I'll keep checking, then.

666
00:45:38,777 --> 00:45:41,822
You'll be safe for now.
They probably won't attack a church.

667
00:45:42,322 --> 00:45:44,616
Stay safe, In-a. Get some rest for now.

668
00:45:46,326 --> 00:45:48,245
-Okay, you stay here.
-Okay.

669
00:45:50,873 --> 00:45:53,459
Hyung. I mean, Father…

670
00:45:53,542 --> 00:45:54,585
Yun-sang.

671
00:45:56,795 --> 00:45:58,338
You two go rest for a bit.

672
00:45:59,423 --> 00:46:00,883
We can switch out at dawn.

673
00:46:26,283 --> 00:46:29,745
Hey, So-min.
You're going to see Ha-yul, right?

674
00:46:30,662 --> 00:46:33,665
Uh, take her some of
the pickled radish she liked.

675
00:46:38,504 --> 00:46:41,173
Here, give this to her.
Take some dried seaweed too.

676
00:46:41,256 --> 00:46:43,342
Auntie, where'd you go?

677
00:46:43,842 --> 00:46:46,303
Oh, Auntie's right here.

678
00:48:14,308 --> 00:48:16,685
What? You're resting here?

679
00:48:21,899 --> 00:48:24,109
I think it's time we talked,
don't you think?

680
00:48:41,251 --> 00:48:43,211
I suppose. Okay.

681
00:48:54,932 --> 00:48:56,808
So what are you gonna do?

682
00:49:00,312 --> 00:49:02,314
Stop talking like it's all on me.

683
00:49:05,442 --> 00:49:06,652
It is though.

684
00:49:09,321 --> 00:49:10,572
And you know it is.

685
00:49:11,823 --> 00:49:14,201
The choice is yours.
I don't know what else to say.

686
00:49:14,826 --> 00:49:16,453
I need to have you with me!

687
00:49:16,536 --> 00:49:17,746
You "need" to?

688
00:49:18,789 --> 00:49:19,998
Is that all I am?

689
00:49:21,166 --> 00:49:22,417
A thing you "need"?

690
00:49:23,377 --> 00:49:24,586
I understand.

691
00:49:25,170 --> 00:49:27,714
I'm just a flower, a tree, a plant.

692
00:49:27,798 --> 00:49:30,217
A thing in the corner
of a painting you made.

693
00:49:31,218 --> 00:49:32,886
You "need" me. Is that it?

694
00:49:39,059 --> 00:49:40,352
Se-kyung, why…

695
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:44,481
You're twisting my words around.
How does that help anything?

696
00:49:47,567 --> 00:49:49,778
Do you really think I could just
leave you behind here?

697
00:49:49,861 --> 00:49:53,323
I'm just a bitch who's crazy!
You gotta leave me behind, Yun-sang!

698
00:49:53,407 --> 00:49:54,616
Wake up already!

699
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:56,535
Se-kyung…

700
00:49:56,618 --> 00:49:59,788
…why do you keep trying to leave me, huh?

701
00:50:00,998 --> 00:50:04,251
Yun-sang. Hey, listen to me. Stop.

702
00:50:04,876 --> 00:50:05,794
Sit down.

703
00:50:15,178 --> 00:50:16,763
I wouldn't be happy.

704
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:23,061
My kids are dead now.

705
00:50:24,896 --> 00:50:26,732
I'm not able to let it go.

706
00:50:27,983 --> 00:50:30,193
I don't think
I can go on living like that.

707
00:50:33,155 --> 00:50:35,157
Only three of my kids are left.

708
00:50:37,284 --> 00:50:38,660
They deserve dignity

709
00:50:39,745 --> 00:50:41,913
and to be safe and taken care of.

710
00:50:41,997 --> 00:50:45,417
And to not get threatened or used
where they end up going

711
00:50:45,500 --> 00:50:46,668
until their very last breath.

712
00:50:46,752 --> 00:50:49,004
And that's why I went
and killed all of those bastards,

713
00:50:49,087 --> 00:50:50,422
those pieces of shit!

714
00:50:51,673 --> 00:50:54,217
Yeah, and I'd do it all again.

715
00:51:04,269 --> 00:51:06,938
I knew, but I still hoped it wasn't true.

716
00:51:08,940 --> 00:51:10,650
-Why did you have to…
-Oh…

717
00:51:11,318 --> 00:51:12,611
Why, Se-kyung?

718
00:51:21,787 --> 00:51:24,623
Did you really think these guys
wouldn't find out what you did?

719
00:51:24,706 --> 00:51:26,625
They probably already know.

720
00:51:27,417 --> 00:51:28,376
Yeah.

721
00:51:29,961 --> 00:51:32,172
They can't kill me yet
because they still need you.

722
00:51:52,067 --> 00:51:53,610
Leave me behind.

723
00:51:58,281 --> 00:52:00,826
Instead of me, take the kids with you.

724
00:52:04,121 --> 00:52:05,247
The kids are innocent.

725
00:52:06,998 --> 00:52:08,834
So take them with you, okay?

726
00:52:10,544 --> 00:52:12,712
I'm being too selfish, aren't I?

727
00:52:15,173 --> 00:52:17,175
They'd hate me for leaving you behind.

728
00:52:17,259 --> 00:52:19,511
I know they're in good hands with you.

729
00:52:20,053 --> 00:52:23,223
They'll treat you well in the safety zone
because of all your skills.

730
00:52:24,683 --> 00:52:27,144
You can take care of them
until they're adults.

731
00:52:28,603 --> 00:52:33,150
I know it's sad to separate them
from their families at such a young age.

732
00:52:35,277 --> 00:52:37,362
But their parents trust you.

733
00:52:37,445 --> 00:52:38,738
They'll be grateful.

734
00:52:39,739 --> 00:52:41,867
They'll be relieved,
knowing their kids are all right.

735
00:52:47,581 --> 00:52:49,541
You know I can't do that!

736
00:52:50,500 --> 00:52:51,585
Don't be cruel.

737
00:52:51,668 --> 00:52:53,795
This is the only thing that gives me hope.

